{%- if rbac_enforce_managed_access == 'Yes' %}

## Actions

| # | Action | Details |
|---|--------|---------|
| 1 | Discover | Identify all schemas without Managed Access |
| 2 | Enable | Generate `ALTER SCHEMA ... ENABLE MANAGED ACCESS` for each |
| 3 | Verify | Confirm all target schemas have Managed Access enabled |

## Impact

After enabling Managed Access:
- Object owners in these schemas **cannot** grant privileges on their objects
- Only the schema owner and SECURITYADMIN can manage grants
- Existing grants remain in effect (no immediate revocation)
- Future privilege management is centralized

## Verification

Run the discovery query after applying changes. Expected result: **zero schemas without Managed Access** in your target scope.

{%- else %}

## Skipped

Managed Access enforcement is disabled. No schemas will be modified.

To enable, set `rbac_enforce_managed_access` to `Yes` in your answer file.

{%- endif %}
